{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_37","type":"command_execution","command":"/usr/bin/bash -lc \"rg -n '3/3|100\\\\.00|LoaderConfigurator|contextLoaderProbe|classLoaderProbe|dynamic-access' /home/vjovanov/c/forge5/metadata-forge/local_repositories/metadata-forge-metrics /home/vjovanov/c/forge5/metadata-forge/local_repositories/forge_run_metrics /home/vjovanov/c/forge5/metadata-forge/script_run_metrics 2>/dev/null\"","aggregated_output":"/home/vjovanov/c/forge5/metadata-forge/local_repositories/metadata-forge-metrics/script_run_metrics/fix_java_run_fail.json:835:      \"analysis_markdown\": \"# Post-generation intervention report\\n\\nLibrary: org.apache.kafka:kafka-streams:3.6.0\\nStage: `metadata_fix_failed`\\n\\n## Summary\\n\\nThe post-generation native test failure was caused by two generated dynamic-access tests that exercise upstream Kafka test classes relying on Mockito's default ByteBuddy mock maker. In Native Image, ByteBuddy tries to define `net.bytebuddy.utility.Invoker$Dispatcher` at runtime, which is an unsupported runtime class-definition feature rather than a missing metadata registration.\\n\\nBased on the Codex metadata-fix log, the earlier metadata gaps had already moved forward enough that they were no longer the blocking failure. The remaining blocker was the unsupported Mockito/ByteBuddy runtime behavior, so the generated tests that depended on that behavior were removed. No metadata files were modified.\\n\\n## Root cause of each failing test\\n\\n### 1. `org.apache.kafka.streams.processor.internals.ReadOnlyTaskTest.shouldThrowUnsupportedOperationExceptionForForbiddenMethods()`\\n\\n- **Root cause:** not metadata-related.\\n- **Why:** the failure is `com.oracle.svm.core.jdk.UnsupportedFeatureError` caused by Mockito/ByteBuddy attempting runtime class generation for `net.bytebuddy.utility.Invoker$Dispatcher`.\\n- **Action taken:** removed generated test `tests/src/org.apache.kafka/kafka-streams/3.6.0/src/test/java/org_apache_kafka/kafka_streams/ReadOnlyTaskTestDynamicAccessTest.java` and its test-only reflection config `tests/src/org.apache.kafka/kafka-streams/3.6.0/src/test/resources/META-INF/native-image/read-only-task-test-dynamic-access/reflect-config.json`.\\n\\n### 2. `org_apache_kafka.kafka_streams.ReadOnlyTaskTestDynamicAccessTest.shouldExerciseReadOnlyTaskReflectionCoverage()`\\n\\n- **Root cause:** follow-on failure, not metadata-related.\\n- **Why:** this generated wrapper test launches the failing upstream `ReadOnlyTaskTest` method and then asserts that the launched test had zero failures. Since the upstream test fails due to ByteBuddy runtime class definition, the wrapper reports `expected: 0L but was: 1L`.\\n- **Action taken:** removed with the same file deletion above.\\n\\n### 3. `org.apache.kafka.streams.state.internals.RocksDBStoreTest.shouldCloseStatisticsWhenUserProvidesNoStatistics()`\\n\\n- **Root cause:** not metadata-related.\\n- **Why:** the primary failure is again Mockito/ByteBuddy runtime class definition in Native Image, not a missing registration. The suppressed `NullPointerException`s in teardown are cleanup fallout after setup never completed.\\n- **Action taken:** removed generated test `tests/src/org.apache.kafka/kafka-streams/3.6.0/src/test/java/org_apache_kafka/kafka_streams/RocksDBStoreTestDynamicAccessTest.java` and its test-only reflection config `tests/src/org.apache.kafka/kafka-streams/3.6.0/src/test/resources/META-INF/native-image/rocksdb-store-test-dynamic-access/reflect-config.json`.\\n\\n### 4. `org_apache_kafka.kafka_streams.RocksDBStoreTestDynamicAccessTest.shouldExerciseRocksDBStoreStatisticsLookup()`\\n\\n- **Root cause:** follow-on failure, not metadata-related.\\n- **Why:** this generated wrapper test launches the failing upstream `RocksDBStoreTest` method and then asserts zero failures. Because the launched test fails for the same Mockito/ByteBuddy native-image limitation, the wrapper fails with `expected: 0L but was: 1L`.\\n- **Action taken:** removed with the same file deletion above.\\n\\n## Why the remaining generated support should be preserved\\n\\nThe remaining generated support still provides useful native coverage for `kafka-streams` without depending on unsupported Mockito/ByteBuddy runtime class generation. After removing only the two problematic generated tests and their test-only configs, `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=org.apache.kafka:kafka-streams:3.6.0 --stacktrace` passed successfully.\\n\\nThat preserved support still validates meaningful reflection and resource usage through the remaining generated tests, including:\\n\\n- `IQv2IntegrationTestDynamicAccessTest`\\n- `IntegrationTestUtilsDynamicAccessTest`\\n- `KStreamImplDynamicAccessTest`\\n- `QueryableStateIntegrationTestDynamicAccessTest`\\n- `TaskAssignorIntegrationTestDynamicAccessTest`\\n- `KafkaStreamsTest`\\n\\nSo the correct intervention here was to remove only the non-portable generated tests, while keeping the rest of the generated support intact.\"\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge5/metadata-forge/local_repositories/forge_run_metrics/2748-a1aa7324/script_run_metrics/add_new_library_support.json:7663:      \"test_file\": \"tests/src/org.apache.commons/commons-lang3/3.11/src/test/java/org_apache_commons/commons_lang3/ClassUtilsTest.java\",\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge5/metadata-forge/local_repositories/forge_run_metrics/2748-a1aa7324/script_run_metrics/add_new_library_support.json:7664:      \"metadata_file\": \"metadata/org.apache.commons/commons-lang3/3.11/reachability-metadata.json\"\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge5/metadata-forge/local_repositories/forge_run_metrics/2748-a1aa7324/script_run_metrics/add_new_library_support.json:7714:      \"analysis_markdown\": \"# Post-generation intervention report\\n\\nLibrary: org.apache.commons:commons-lang3:3.11\\nStage: metadata_fix_failed\\n\\n## Summary\\n\\nThe generated support failed in native test execution because `EventListenerSupportTest.serializationRoundTripDropsNonSerializableListenersAndRecreatesTransientFields()` hit a GraalVM native-image serialization/reflection limitation during `ObjectInputStream` deserialization.\\n\\n## Failure analysis\\n\\n### Failing test\\n\\n- `tests/src/org.apache.commons/commons-lang3/3.11/src/test/java/org_apache_commons/commons_lang3/EventListenerSupportTest.java`\\n\\n### Root cause\\n\\nThis failure is **not a normal metadata gap** in the generated library support.\\n\\nThe Gradle failure shows `MissingReflectionRegistrationError` for `java.lang.Object.<init>()` from:\\n\\n- `java.io.ObjectStreamClass.newInstance(...)`\\n- `java.io.ObjectInputStream.readOrdinaryObject(...)`\\n\\nThe Codex metadata-fix log shows that it already tried the obvious metadata-based remedies:\\n\\n- adding reflection metadata for `java.lang.Object` default construction,\\n- marking the serialized test class for unsafe allocation,\\n- adding equivalent test-local metadata under `src/test/resources/META-INF/native-image`.\\n\\nDespite that, the runtime still failed with the exact same `java.lang.Object()` error. That means this test is exercising a native-image/JDK deserialization path that is not resolved by the suggested metadata entry, rather than exposing unfinished commons-lang3 metadata.\\n\\n## Intervention\\n\\nRemoved the unsupported generated test:\\n\\n- `tests/src/org.apache.commons/commons-lang3/3.11/src/test/java/org_apache_commons/commons_lang3/EventListenerSupportTest.java`\\n\\nNo metadata files were modified as part of this intervention.\\n\\n## Why the remaining generated support should be preserved\\n\\nThe failure was isolated to one serialization round-trip scenario. The native test report shows the rest of the generated commons-lang3 support working: 52 other tests passed, including coverage for reflection-heavy APIs such as:\\n\\n- `AnnotationUtils`\\n- `ClassUtils`\\n- `ConstructorUtils`\\n- `EqualsBuilder`\\n- `FieldUtils`\\n- `HashCodeBuilder`\\n- `MethodUtils`\\n- `ReflectionToStringBuilder`\\n- `SerializationUtils`\\n- `TypeUtils`\\n\\nThat passing coverage indicates the generated metadata and tests still provide meaningful support for `org.apache.commons:commons-lang3:3.11`. Only the `EventListenerSupport` serialization test should be dropped because it depends on a native-image deserialization behavior that Codex could not fix through metadata registration.\"\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge5/metadata-forge/local_repositories/forge_run_metrics/2748-a1aa7324/script_run_metrics/add_new_library_support.json:7728:      \"test_file\": \"tests/src/org.apache.commons/commons-lang3/3.11/src/test/java/org_apache_commons/commons_lang3/CompareToBuilderTest.java\",\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge5/metadata-forge/local_repositories/forge_run_metrics/2748-a1aa7324/script_run_metrics/add_new_library_support.json:7729:      \"metadata_file\": \"metadata/org.apache.commons/commons-lang3/3.11/reachability-metadata.json\"\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge5/metadata-forge/local_repositories/forge_run_metrics/2748-a1aa7324/script_run_metrics/fix_java_run_fail.json:835:      \"analysis_markdown\": \"# Post-generation intervention report\\n\\nLibrary: org.apache.kafka:kafka-streams:3.6.0\\nStage: `metadata_fix_failed`\\n\\n## Summary\\n\\nThe post-generation native test failure was caused by two generated dynamic-access tests that exercise upstream Kafka test classes relying on Mockito's default ByteBuddy mock maker. In Native Image, ByteBuddy tries to define `net.bytebuddy.utility.Invoker$Dispatcher` at runtime, which is an unsupported runtime class-definition feature rather than a missing metadata registration.\\n\\nBased on the Codex metadata-fix log, the earlier metadata gaps had already moved forward enough that they were no longer the blocking failure. The remaining blocker was the unsupported Mockito/ByteBuddy runtime behavior, so the generated tests that depended on that behavior were removed. No metadata files were modified.\\n\\n## Root cause of each failing test\\n\\n### 1. `org.apache.kafka.streams.processor.internal